ggplot() + 
  geom_dumbbell(
    data=Broncos, 
    aes(y=reorder(Name, W), x=W, xend=L),
    size = 2,
    colour = "grey",
    colour_x = "green",
    colour_xend = "red") +
  labs(
    title="Broncos QBs records", 
    subtitle = "If &lt;span style = 'color:green;'&gt;W&lt;/span&gt; are on the right, that's good. If &lt;span style = 'color:red;'&gt;L&lt;/span&gt; are on the right, that's bad.",
    x= "Wins and Losses",
    y="Player",
    caption="Source: Matt Waite | By Logan Kuker"
  ) + 
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(
    plot.subtitle = element_textbox_simple()
      ) +
 theme(
    plot.title = element_text(size = 20, face = "bold"),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 8)
    ) 









Peyton Manning’s record is extremely good at 45-12 compared to the other QBs having less losses than some of them have wins. The worst QB record by a Broncos QB starting at least eight games is Joe Flacco at 2-6.
